  "question": "Are fire brigade interventions in Belgium free or paid?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Fire brigade interventions in Belgium are legally regulated. While most services are free, certain interventions may incur costs depending on their nature and the local municipality's regulations."
    },
    {
                      "type": "image",
                      "url": "https://www.mensura.be/uploads/cache/hero/uploads/media/624ae33929048/brandveiligheid-preventie-en-bestrijding.png?v1"
             },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### When Are Fire Brigade Services Free?\nFire brigade services are always free for:\n- Fires.\n- Explosions.\n- Rescuing people in distress (e.g., saving a drowning person)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### When Do You Have to Pay for Fire Brigade Services?\n- Municipalities are required to charge for non-legally mandated interventions performed by their fire brigades.\n- Some legally mandated interventions may also be charged, as specified in the municipality's fee regulations (retributiereglement).\n\nExamples of paid services include:\n- Urgent medical assistance.\n- Environmental pollution (charged to the operator or owner of the polluting materials).\n- Rescuing animals.\n- Pumping water from a basement due to poor maintenance of water pipes.\n- Removing wasp nests."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For more information, contact your municipality or local fire brigade."
