  "question": "How can you join the Flemish Social Protection system?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The Flemish Social Protection (Vlaamse Sociale Bescherming) system is mandatory for certain individuals residing in Flanders. It provides support for long-term care and assistance. Here's what you need to know about joining."
    },
    {
                      "type": "image",
                      "url": "https://admin.expatica.com/be/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2023/11/social-security-belgium.jpg"
             },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Who Must Join?\nYou must join the Flemish Social Protection system if you:\n- Are **26 years or older**.\n- **Live in Flanders**, meaning you are registered in the population or foreigners' register of a Flemish municipality.\n- Maintain an address in Flanders, even if you temporarily reside abroad.\n\nYou are required to join even if you are registered in Flanders for just one day."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Exceptions\n1. **Outgoing Cross-Border Workers:**\n   - Membership is not mandatory but allowed if you:\n     - Are 26 or older.\n     - Live in Flanders.\n     - Are socially insured through work in another EU member state, EEA country, or Switzerland.\n   - Dependents can also voluntarily join.\n\n2. **Employees of International Institutions:**\n   - Joining is not possible if you are insured under the social security system of the EU (e.g., for EU officials) or institutions like NATO or the United Nations.\n   - Membership is allowed if you opt for the Belgian social security system.\n\n3. **Foreign Students:**\n   - **From EU/EEA/Switzerland:** Joining is optional if you are 26 or older.\n   - **From Other Countries:**\n     - Temporary residents with student or researcher permits cannot join.\n     - If you do not have a temporary residence permit, you must join if living in Flanders. Voluntary membership is possible if living in Brussels."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### How to Join?\nTo join the Flemish Social Protection system, you must register with one of six recognized care funds (zorgkassen):\n- **Care fund linked to your health insurance:**\n  - Christelijke Mutualiteiten-Zorgkas Vlaanderen\n  - Neutrale Zorgkas Vlaanderen\n  - Solidaris Zorgkas\n  - Liberale Ziekenfondsen Zorgkas\n  - Onafhankelijke Ziekenfondsen Zorgkas\n- **Vlaamse Zorgkas:** Automatically assigned if you are required to join but fail to do so voluntarily.\n\nYou will receive an invitation from your care fund to pay the care premium in the year you turn 26 or move to Flanders. Membership is confirmed upon your first payment. Subsequently, you will receive an annual payment request from your care fund."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Legal Framework\nThe Flemish Social Protection system is governed by the decree of May 18, 2018."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.vlaanderen.be/vlaamse-sociale-bescherming"
    }
