{
  "question": "What is the annual care premium for the Flemish Social Protection system, and what happens if you do not pay it?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The annual care premium is a mandatory payment for those registered with the Flemish Social Protection system. The premium supports services for long-term care and assistance."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Amount\n- In 2024, the care premium is **€62**.\n- A reduced premium may apply if you meet specific conditions.\n- No premium is required if you:\n  - Are in a collective debt settlement (CSR) or personal bankruptcy.\n  - Are administratively registered but not required to join."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Administrative Registration\nAdministrative registration applies to individuals:\n- Residing in a care center, day care center, or short-stay center.\n- Using a mobility aid (MOHM).\n\nAdministrative registration is not possible for those who are ineligible for the Flemish Social Protection system."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Payment Deadline\nThe care premium must be paid by **April 30** each year. Exceptions include:\n- Turning 26: You have until July 1 of that year to register.\n- Moving to Flanders: You have six months from the registration date in the national register.\n- Moving to Brussels: The same six-month rule applies.\n- Incorrect address: Payment is due by the date on the updated payment request."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Penalties for Non-Payment\n- Missing two annual payments (not necessarily consecutive) results in a **€250 fine**.\n- Steps before a fine:\n  - A reminder is sent by registered mail or via eBox, with payment due by **October 5**.\n  - Failure to pay leads to a final warning from the Flemish Social Protection Agency. Payment must include all arrears and fines within two months.\n  - A bailiff may be involved if payment is not made.\n- The fine is reduced to **€100** if you qualify for increased reimbursement from health insurance."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Appeals\nYou can appeal a fine if:\n- You can prove you were not obligated to pay the premium.\n- You had a valid reason, such as bankruptcy or a debt settlement.\n- The premium was incorrectly charged.\n\nSubmit your appeal using the online form and include supporting documents. The appeal process suspends the fine's payment deadline."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Payment Plans\nIf you cannot pay the full balance at once, you can request a payment plan to spread the balance over 12 months. Contact the Flemish Social Protection Agency to apply for a payment plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.vlaanderen.be/vlaamse-sociale-bescherming"
    }
  ]
