  "question": "How can you obtain, maintain, or replace mobility aids through the Flemish Social Protection system?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Mobility aids, such as wheelchairs, scooters, or walking aids, can be purchased or rented through the Flemish Social Protection system for those with chronic illnesses, disabilities, or age-related mobility issues. These aids are intended for long-term use and must meet specific conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Types of Mobility Aids Available\n- **Manual Wheelchairs:** Standard, modular, or care wheelchairs, including those for children.\n- **Electronic Wheelchairs:** With motors controlled via joysticks, available for indoor and outdoor use.\n- **Electronic Scooters:** For mobility both indoors and outdoors.\n- **Three-Wheel or Four-Wheel Bicycles:** For those unable to use a standard two-wheeler.\n- **Walking Aids:** With or without wheels, providing support for standing or walking.\n- **Standing Systems:** Electrically adjustable standing tables for support in upright positions.\n\nTemporary aids, such as crutches, are not covered under this program."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Conditions for Eligibility\n- **Medical Condition:**\n  - A doctor or wheelchair advisory team must assess your health to determine your eligibility and the appropriate type of aid.\n  - Those with rapidly degenerative conditions, such as ALS, can access expedited rental options upon verification by a neurologist or specialized team.\n\n- **Administrative Requirements:**\n  - You must be registered with the Flemish Social Protection system and pay the annual care premium.\n\n- **Exceptions:**\n  - Temporary residents without a national register number must obtain a BIS number.\n  - Hospitalized individuals cannot apply until their discharge.\n  - Residents of psychiatric facilities or those in Brussels/Flanders can apply if registered with the system."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### How to Apply for a Mobility Aid\n1. **Obtain a Prescription:**\n   - Visit your doctor or a specialized advisory team for an assessment and prescription.\n\n2. **Visit a Certified Supplier:**\n   - Present your prescription to a recognized supplier who will propose a suitable aid.\n   - Test the device before purchase, especially for electronic wheelchairs or scooters.\n\n3. **Submit Your Application:**\n   - The supplier will help complete and submit the application, including any required reports.\n\n4. **Wait for Approval:**\n   - Approval typically takes 10-20 working days, though additional reviews may extend this period.\n   - For non-listed aids, approval may take up to 45 working days."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Maintenance and Replacement\n- **Maintenance:**\n  - Costs are partially covered for purchased aids, with a standard maintenance allowance of €150 for wheelchairs and bicycles, and €250 for scooters.\n  - For rented aids, maintenance is included in the rental fee.\n\n- **Replacement:**\n  - Aids can be replaced after a set period, depending on the type of aid and your age.\n  - Early replacement is possible for rapid health deterioration or excessive wear due to frequent use."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Appeals and Financial Support\n- If your application is denied, you can appeal to the labor court.\n- Financial assistance for maintenance, repair, or replacement is available under specific conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.vlaanderen.be/vlaamse-sociale-bescherming"
    }
