    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Preventing Mental Health Problems\n- **Strengthen resilience** to better handle stress and challenges through initiatives like:\n  - **Zilverwijzer Group Sessions:** For individuals over 60.\n  - **Goed-Gevoel-Stoel:** A program for addressing challenges related to finances, health, and social inclusion.\n  - **Family Platform:** Support for families and friends of people with mental health or addiction issues.\n  - **Youth-Focused Resources:**\n    - Noknok.be for teens aged 12-16.\n    - Familieplatform KOPP for children of parents with mental health issues.\n    - Tweehuizen.be for children and teens dealing with parental separation."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Talking Anonymously About Your Concerns\n- **Tele-Onthaal:** Call 106 or chat anonymously for support.\n- **Awel:** A helpline for youth, available at 102 or via chat.\n- **Werkgroep Verder:** Online support for those affected by suicide.\n- **The Drugline:** Assistance with addiction-related questions at 078 15 10 20 or through chat."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Help for Suicidal Thoughts\n- **Zelfmoordlijn (Suicide Hotline):** Call 1813, chat daily from 17:00 to midnight, or visit www.zelfmoord1813.be.\n- **Thinklife:** An online self-help course for managing suicidal thoughts."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### First-Line Help\n- **General Practitioner (GP):** Your GP is often the first point of contact for mental health concerns and can refer you to specialized care.\n- **CAW (General Welfare Centers):** Accessible and supportive centers for psychosocial issues.\n- **CLB (Pupil Guidance Centers):** Support for children and teens with issues like bullying or anxiety.\n- **Self-Help Groups:** Connect with others facing similar challenges through Trefpunt Zelfhulp, which offers groups for various conditions, including eating disorders, autism, and gambling addiction."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Specialized Care\n- **Centers for Mental Health Care (CGG):** Teams of psychiatrists, psychologists, and social workers offer support for severe mental health issues.\n- **Psychiatric Hospitals:** For intensive treatment, with multidisciplinary teams available.\n- **Private Practitioners:** Psychiatrists and psychologists also operate privately and can be accessed through GP referrals."
