{
  "question": "What is the equivalent subsistence income (equivalent leefloon), and how can you apply for it in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The equivalent subsistence income (equivalent leefloon) provides financial support for individuals who are not eligible for the regular leefloon due to not meeting one or more conditions but are in a similar situation of insufficient means, preventing societal integration. The amount received under this scheme is equivalent to the leefloon, subject to specific conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Eligibility Criteria\nTo qualify for the equivalent leefloon, you must meet the following conditions:\n- **Residency:** Have an actual residence in Belgium and hold a valid residence permit.\n- **No Leefloon Eligibility:** You are not entitled to the standard leefloon or social integration.\n- **Emergency Situation:** You are unable to secure basic needs such as shelter, food, clothing, hygiene, or access to healthcare.\n\nThe OCMW may impose additional conditions for granting the equivalent leefloon."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Application Procedure\n1. **Contact the OCMW:** Visit the OCMW office in your municipality and express your interest in the equivalent leefloon.\n2. **Initial Interview:** A social worker will discuss your situation to understand your needs.\n3. **Social Investigation:** A detailed investigation will assess your eligibility. Your active cooperation is required.\n4. **Decision:** The OCMW decides whether to grant the equivalent leefloon or suggest alternative support options."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Required Documents\nWhen visiting the OCMW, bring the following:\n- Identity card.\n- Proof of current income (if applicable) for yourself and household members (excluding minor children).\n- An overview of your savings.\n\nThe social worker may request additional documents based on your case."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Financial Support\nThe amount of the equivalent leefloon depends on your household situation and falls into one of three categories:\n1. **Cohabiting:** Sharing household expenses (e.g., rent, utilities) with someone else, not necessarily a partner.\n2. **Single:** Living alone.\n3. **Cohabiting with Dependent Child(ren):** Supporting at least one minor, unmarried child. If you have a partner, the amount applies to both of you."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The exact amount is adjusted for your household income and is consistent across all OCMWs in Belgium."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.mi-is.be/"
    }
