  "question": "What is an advance directive for euthanasia, and how can it be set up in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "An advance directive for euthanasia allows you to request euthanasia if you permanently lose consciousness. Without this directive, euthanasia can only be performed at the explicit request of a patient capable of expressing their will to die."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Conditions\nYou can create an advance directive if you meet the following criteria:\n- **Age:** You are of legal age (or emancipated minor).\n- **Capacity:** You are legally competent to make decisions.\n- **Form Requirements:**\n  - Use the legally prescribed form.\n  - The directive must be signed less than five years before the onset of incapacity.\n  - It must be made voluntarily, without external pressure.\n  - Two adult witnesses must be present, one of whom has no material interest in your death.\n\nEuthanasia based on this directive is only allowed if the patient is in a state of irreversible coma. It is not applicable in cases of acquired incapacity due to conditions like dementia or brain tumors."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Procedure\n1. **Obtain the Form:** Download the form or get it from your local Civil Affairs department.\n2. **Complete and Sign:**\n   - Fill out the directive in the presence of two witnesses (at least one without material benefit from your death).\n   - Optionally, designate one or more trusted persons to inform the treating physician when the directive should be enacted.\n   - Date and sign the form along with the witnesses and any trusted persons.\n3. **Distribute Copies:** Create multiple copies to ensure accessibility for relatives and treating physicians. You may optionally register a copy at your municipal office.\n\n- **Validity:**\n  - Directives dated **from April 2, 2020, onwards** are valid indefinitely.\n  - Directives dated **before April 2, 2020,** are valid for five years and can be updated to an indefinite version.\n\nYou can revise or revoke the directive at any time."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Oversight and Compliance\nThe Federal Commission for Control and Evaluation ensures that euthanasia is carried out under the conditions and procedures specified by law. For more information, visit the [Federal Public Service for Health](https://www.health.belgium.be/)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Required Documents\nIf registering the directive at your municipal office, bring:\n- The signed directive form.\n- The identity card of the person making the directive."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Cost\nRegistering an advance directive for euthanasia is free of charge."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.health.belgium.be/"
    }
