  "question": "What are the necessary arrangements after the death of a loved one in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The death of a loved one is an emotional time, but it also requires practical arrangements. Here is an overview of steps to take immediately after a death, funeral arrangements, and handling the deceased's estate."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Immediately After Death\n1. **Death Certification:**\n   - A physician must certify the death and issue a medical death certificate. This document will include the date, time, and cause of death.\n2. **Report the Death:**\n   - The death must be reported to the Civil Registry in the municipality where the death occurred. Relatives or a funeral director can handle this.\n3. **Receive a Death Certificate:**\n   - After registration, you will receive an official death certificate."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Arranging the Funeral\n1. **Consider the Deceased's Wishes:**\n   - Check for funeral preferences in a will, a written declaration (wilsbeschikking), or pre-arranged plans with a funeral director.\n   - Note that if preferences are in a will, they might not be known until after the funeral.\n2. **Decide on Burial or Cremation:**\n   - Choose between burial or cremation based on the deceased's wishes or family decisions.\n3. **Special Arrangements:**\n   - If the body needs to be transported abroad, apply for the necessary permits and follow the requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Notify Institutions\nInform the following parties about the death:\n- **Bank:** Notify all banks where the deceased had accounts. Accounts will be frozen until heirs are identified.\n- **Employer:** If the deceased was employed.\n- **Health Insurance:** Notify the deceased's health insurance provider.\n- **DIV (Vehicle Registration):** Return the license plate and update the vehicle registration.\n- **Insurance Companies:** Inform any relevant insurance providers.\n- **Notary:** Consult a notary for matters involving a will, inheritance agreements, or marital contracts.\n- **Family Allowance Fund (Groeipakket):** Notify them to prevent overpayments."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Estate and Inheritance\n1. **Contact a Notary:**\n   - The notary will identify heirs and advise on accepting or renouncing the estate.\n   - They will handle the inventory of the estate and guide you through inheritance decisions.\n2. **Inheritance Taxes:**\n   - Inheritance taxes must be paid based on the value of the deceased’s assets in Belgium.\n   - File a declaration of inheritance to calculate the due taxes for each heir."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Survivor's Pension\nIf the deceased was married, the surviving spouse may be entitled to a survivor’s pension based on the deceased’s career. Check eligibility and apply through the relevant pension scheme."
