  "question": "What is the procedure for reporting a death in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A death must be registered with the Civil Registry of the municipality where the person passed away. This process, called a 'death declaration,' formalizes the death and creates an official death certificate."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Procedure\n1. **Medical Certification:**\n   - A doctor must confirm the death and issue a death certificate.\n   - If the death occurs at home, contact the general practitioner or on-call doctor.\n   - In hospitals or care facilities, the institution arranges for the certificate.\n   - For accidental or suspicious deaths, the police draft a report in the presence of a doctor.\n2. **Death Declaration:**\n   - The death must be reported as soon as possible to the Civil Registry of the municipality where the person passed away.\n   - Usually, a funeral director handles the declaration and administrative processes, but relatives can do this themselves.\n   - The Civil Registry official issues an official death certificate upon registration."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Required Documents\nBring the following documents for the death declaration:\n- Medical death certificate issued by the doctor.\n- Identity card of the deceased.\n- Identity card of the person reporting the death.\n- Driver's license of the deceased (if applicable).\n- Last will and testament of the deceased (if available).\n\nFor suspicious or violent deaths, also bring:\n- Police report.\n- Burial or cremation authorization from the public prosecutor."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Notify Other Parties\nIn addition to the Civil Registry, inform the following:\n- Bank\n- Notary\n- Insurance companies\n- Health insurance provider\n- Pension service\n- Tax authorities\n- Landlord\n- Utility providers (water, gas, electricity)\n- Employer"
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.belgium.be/en/family/death/registration"
    }
