{
  "question": "What are the eligibility criteria and procedures for a survivor's pension in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A survivor's pension provides financial support to the surviving spouse or dependent children of a deceased individual. The pension is available regardless of whether the deceased was already retired or not. It is sometimes referred to as a widow's or widower's pension."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Eligibility Criteria\n**For spouses:**\n- **Minimum age:** You must meet the minimum age requirement at the time of your spouse's death. In 2023, this is 49 years and increases by six months annually. Exceptions apply if you already receive a personal pension.\n- **Marital duration:** You must have been married for at least one year unless exceptions apply (e.g., a child in common, legal cohabitation before marriage lasting at least one year, etc.).\n- **No remarriage:** The pension is suspended if you remarry.\n- **No criminal conviction:** You must not have been convicted of offenses against the deceased.\n\n**For children (orphans):**\n- The deceased must have been a civil servant.\n- Full orphans (both parents deceased) or equivalent status (e.g., a surviving parent without entitlement to a survivor's pension).\n- Must be under 18 years old or eligible for child benefits if older.\n- Must not have been convicted of offenses against the deceased."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Application Procedure\n**For non-civil servants:**\n- Submit your application via:\n  - The municipal administration.\n  - The relevant pension authority.\n  - Online at [mypension.be](https://www.mypension.be).\n- Applications must be submitted within 12 months of the death.\n\n**For civil servants:**\n- If the deceased was an active employee, apply through their last government employer or directly to the Federal Pension Service (FPD).\n- If the deceased was retired, the Federal Pension Service automatically opens a survivor's pension file for the surviving spouse."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Required Documents\n- Identity card with PIN.\n- Bank account details for payment."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Calculation\nThe amount depends on factors such as:\n- The number of eligible recipients.\n- Guaranteed minimum amounts.\n- Income limits (for civil servants).\n- Other income sources (employment or benefits)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Exceptions and Special Cases\n- **Transitional allowance:** If you meet all criteria except the minimum age, you may qualify for a transitional allowance.\n- **Temporary survivor’s pension:** Available for spouses of civil servants who were not married for at least one year. This is granted for 12 months.\n- **Ex-spouses:** Ex-spouses of civil servants can also apply if they meet specific conditions. The pension may be divided between the ex-spouse and the surviving spouse, with applications required within 12 months of the death."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.mypension.be"
    }
  ]
